Overview of Improvements

    Custom Hooks: We'll move the itinerary and insight logic into useItinerary and useMarketInsights hooks.

    Validation Logic: Move validation out of the component to make it testable and clean.

    Component Extraction: Extract the Error Banner into its own component to reduce JSX clutter.

    Performance: Use useCallback to prevent unnecessary re-renders of child components like InputForm.

1. The Validation Helper (utils/validation.ts)

Moving the logic here makes the main component much easier to read.
TypeScript

import { TripFormData, ValidationErrors } from '../types';

export const validateTripData = (data: TripFormData): ValidationErrors => {
  const errors: ValidationErrors = {};

  if (!data.origin?.trim()) {
    errors.origin = { 
      message: "Origin is required", 
      suggestion: "Enter a starting city (e.g., 'New York, NY')" 
    };
  }

  if (!data.destination?.trim()) {
    errors.destination = { 
      message: "Destination is required", 
      suggestion: "Enter a destination city" 
    };
  }

  if (data.startDate && data.endDate) {
    const start = new Date(`${data.startDate}T00:00:00Z`);
    const end = new Date(`${data.endDate}T00:00:00Z`);
    if (start > end) {
      errors.startDate = { message: "Invalid date range", suggestion: "Start date must be before Return date" };
      errors.endDate = { message: "Invalid date range", suggestion: "Return date must be after Start date" };
    }
  }

  return errors;
};

2. Custom Logic Hook (hooks/useItinerary.ts)

This encapsulates all the "brains" of the itinerary generation.
TypeScript

import { useState, useCallback } from 'react';
import { TripFormData, Itinerary, ValidationErrors } from '../types';
import { generateItinerary } from '../services/geminiService';
import { validateTripData } from '../utils/validation';

export const useItinerary = () => {
  const [itinerary, setItinerary] = useState<Itinerary | null>(null);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [validationErrors, setValidationErrors] = useState<ValidationErrors>({});
  const [lastData, setLastData] = useState<TripFormData | null>(null);

  const handleGenerate = useCallback(async (data: TripFormData, isAlternative: boolean) => {
    setIsLoading(true);
    setError(null);

    const errors = validateTripData(data);
    if (Object.keys(errors).length > 0) {
      setValidationErrors(errors);
      setIsLoading(false);
      return false; // Indicate failure
    }

    setValidationErrors({});
    setLastData(data);

    try {
      const result = await generateItinerary(data, isAlternative);
      setItinerary(result);
      return true; // Indicate success
    } catch (err: any) {
      setError(err.message || "Failed to generate itinerary.");
      return false;
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  }, []);

  return { itinerary, isLoading, error, validationErrors, lastData, handleGenerate, setError };
};

3. Refactored App Component

By using the hooks above, your App.tsx becomes much more declarative and easier to maintain.
TypeScript

import React, { useState, useCallback } from 'react';
import { InputForm } from './components/InputForm';
import { ItineraryDisplay } from './components/ItineraryDisplay';
import { MarketInsights } from './components/MarketInsights';
import { ErrorBanner } from './components/ErrorBanner'; // Extracted this
import { useItinerary } from './hooks/useItinerary';
import { useMarketInsights } from './hooks/useMarketInsights'; // Similar to useItinerary
import { DEFAULT_FORM_DATA } from './constants';
import { MapPin, TrendingUp, Compass } from 'lucide-react';

type ViewMode = 'planner' | 'insights';

const App: React.FC = () => {
  const [currentView, setCurrentView] = useState<ViewMode>('planner');
  const [showResultsMobile, setShowResultsMobile] = useState(false);

  const { 
    itinerary, isLoading, error, validationErrors, 
    lastData, handleGenerate, setError 
  } = useItinerary();

  const { insights, isInsightsLoading, fetchInsights } = useMarketInsights();

  const onFormSubmit = async (data: any, isAlt: boolean) => {
    const success = await handleGenerate(data, isAlt);
    if (success && window.innerWidth < 1024) {
      setShowResultsMobile(true);
    }
  };

  const switchView = (view: ViewMode) => {
    setCurrentView(view);
    if (view === 'insights' && !insights) fetchInsights();
  };

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col h-screen bg-gray-50 text-[#222222]">
      {/* Header Section */}
      <header className="flex-none bg-white border-b border-gray-200 z-50 sticky top-0">
        <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 h-20 flex items-center justify-between">
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#FF385C] cursor-pointer" onClick={() => switchView('planner')}>
            <MapPin className="w-8 h-8 fill-current" />
            <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold hidden sm:block">RoadTripPro</h1>
          </div>

          <nav className="flex items-center gap-6">
            <NavButton 
              active={currentView === 'planner'} 
              onClick={() => switchView('planner')} 
              icon={<Compass className="w-4 h-4" />}
              label="Plan a Trip" 
            />
            <NavButton 
              active={currentView === 'insights'} 
              onClick={() => switchView('insights')} 
              icon={<TrendingUp className="w-4 h-4" />}
              label="Market Insights" 
            />
          </nav>
        </div>
      </header>

      <main className="flex-1 overflow-hidden relative">
        <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto h-full p-0 lg:p-6">
          {currentView === 'planner' ? (
            <div className="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-8 h-full">
              {/* Form Column */}
              <div className={`w-full lg:w-[400px] flex-none h-full bg-white transition-transform duration-300 ${showResultsMobile ? '-translate-x-full absolute' : 'translate-x-0 relative'} lg:translate-x-0 lg:relative`}>
                <InputForm 
                  initialData={DEFAULT_FORM_DATA} 
                  onSubmit={onFormSubmit}
                  isLoading={isLoading}
                  validationErrors={validationErrors}
                />
                {error && <ErrorBanner message={error} onClose={() => setError(null)} />}
              </div>

              {/* Display Column */}
              <div className={`flex-1 h-full transition-transform duration-300 ${showResultsMobile ? 'translate-x-0 absolute inset-0 z-30' : 'translate-x-full absolute'} lg:translate-x-0 lg:relative`}>
                {showResultsMobile && (
                   <button onClick={() => setShowResultsMobile(false)} className="lg:hidden absolute top-4 left-4 z-50 bg-white px-4 py-2 rounded-full shadow-md">
                     ← Edit Plan
                   </button>
                )}
                <ItineraryDisplay 
                  itinerary={itinerary} 
                  isLoading={isLoading} 
                  onGenerateAlternative={() => lastData && onFormSubmit(lastData, true)}
                />
              </div>
            </div>
          ) : (
            <MarketInsights insights={insights} isLoading={isInsightsLoading} onRefresh={fetchInsights} />
          )}
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  );
};

// Small helper component for navigation
const NavButton: React.FC<{ active: boolean, onClick: () => void, icon: React.ReactNode, label: string }> = ({ active, onClick, icon, label }) => (
  <button 
    onClick={onClick}
    className={`py-2 transition-colors flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold ${active ? 'text-gray-900 border-b-2 border-gray-900' : 'text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-800'}`}
  >
    {icon}
    {label}
  </button>
);

export default App;

Key Accuracy Improvements Explained:

    Timezone Robustness: In your validation, you used ${data.startDate}T00:00:00Z. This is excellent practice as it prevents "off-by-one-day" errors caused by local browser timezones.

    State Synchronization: By creating lastData and passing it to the onGenerateAlternative function, you ensure that "Try again" or "Generate Alt" buttons always use the exact parameters that created the current view.

    UI Feedback: The ErrorBanner component (which you should create by moving that large block of red-50 JSX) handles the specific logic of mapping error strings to user-friendly suggestions.

    Decoupling: The logic for "Insights" and "Planner" no longer live in the same scope. If you want to change how insights are fetched, you only touch useMarketInsights, reducing the risk of breaking the Planner.

